@startuml sequence_test_execution
!theme plain

title Unit Test Isolation Pattern

participant "xUnit Runner" as runner
participant "Test Class" as test
participant "NSubstitute" as mock
participant "SUT (System Under Test)" as sut

== Setup ==
runner -> test : Construct test class
test -> mock : Create mock dependencies\n(IServiceProvider, ILogger, IFileSystem)
test -> sut : Instantiate SUT with mocks

== Execute ==
runner -> test : Invoke test method
test -> mock : Configure returns / expectations
test -> sut : Call method under test
sut -> mock : Calls dependency (if any)
mock --> sut : Returns configured value
sut --> test : Returns result

== Assert ==
test -> test : Assert result matches expected
test -> mock : Verify interactions (optional)
test --> runner : Pass / Fail

== Teardown ==
runner -> test : Dispose (if IDisposable)

note right of mock
  No DI container.
  No file system I/O.
  No process spawning.
  Pure in-memory execution.
end note

@enduml
